%F A013661 Limit_{n->oo} (1/n)*(Sum_{k=1..n} frac((n/k)^(1/2))) = zeta(2) and in general we have lim_{n->oo} (1/n)*(Sum_{k=1..n} frac((n/k)^(1/m))) = zeta(m), m >= 2. - _Yalcin Aktar_, Jul 14 2005
%F A013661 Equals Integral_{x=0..1} (log(x)/(x-1)) dx or Integral_{x>=1} (log(x/(x-1))/x) dx. - _Jean-François Alcover_, May 30 2013
%F A013661 For s >= 2 (including Complex), zeta(s) = Product_{n >= 1} prime(n)^s/(prime(n)^s - 1). - _Fred Daniel Kline_, Apr 10 2014
%F A013661 Also equals 1 + Sum_{n>=0} (-1)^n*StieltjesGamma(n)/n!. - _Jean-François Alcover_, May 07 2014
%F A013661 zeta(2) = Sum_{n>=1} ((floor(sqrt(n)) - floor(sqrt(n-1)))/n). - _Mikael Aaltonen_, Jan 10 2015
%F A013661 zeta(2) = Sum_{n>=1} (((sqrt(5)-1)/2/sqrt(5))^n/n^2) + Sum_{n>=1} (((sqrt(5)+1)/2/sqrt(5))^n/ n^2) + log((sqrt(5)-1)/2/sqrt(5))log((sqrt(5)+1)/2/sqrt(5)). - _Seiichi Kirikami_, Oct 14 2015
%F A013661 The above formula can also be written zeta(2) = dilog(x) + dilog(y) + log(x)*log(y) where x = (1-1/sqrt(5))/2 and y=(1+1/sqrt(5))/2. - _Peter Luschny_, Oct 16 2015
%F A013661 zeta(2) = Integral_{x>=0} 1/(1 + e^x^(1/2)) dx, because (1 - 1/2^(s-1))*Gamma[1 + s]*Zeta[s] = Integral_{x>=0} 1/(1 + e^x^(1/s)) dx. After _Jean-François Alcover_ in A002162. - _Mats Granvik_, Sep 12 2016
%F A013661 zeta(2) = Product_{n >= 1} (144*n^4)/(144*n^4 - 40*n^2 + 1). - _Fred Daniel Kline_, Oct 29 2016
%F A013661 zeta(2) = lim_{n->oo} (1/n) * Sum_{k=1..n} A017665(k)/A017666(k). - _Dimitri Papadopoulos_, May 10 2019 [See the Walfisz reference, and a comment in A284648, citing also the Sándor et al. Handbook. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Aug 22 2019]
%F A013661 Equals Sum_{k>=1} H(k)/(k*(k+1)), where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number. - _Amiram Eldar_, Aug 16 2020
%F A013661 Equals (8/3)*(1/2)!^4 = (8/3)*Gamma(3/2)^4. - _Gary W. Adamson_, Aug 17 2021
%F A013661 Equals ((m+1)/m) * Integral_{x=0..1} log(Sum _{k=0..m} x^k )/x dx, m > 0 (Aubonnet reference). - _Bernard Schott_, Feb 11 2022
%F A013661 Equals 1 + Sum_{n>=1} n*(zeta(n+2)-1). - _Richard R. Forberg_, Jun 04 2023; improved by _Natalia L. Skirrow_, Jul 25 2025
%F A013661 Equals Psi'(1) where Psi'(x) is the trigamma function (by Abramowitz Stegun 6.4.2). - _Andrea Pinos_, Oct 22 2024
%F A013661 Equals Integral_{x=0..1} Integral_{y=0..1} 1/(1 - x*y) dy dx. - _Kritsada Moomuang_, May 22 2025
